<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">856e.00/9–2048: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Consulate
                                        General</gloss> at Batavia</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-22T19:00:00-04:00">September 22, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>443. Estimate situation Repub <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>
                                811, Sep 20, appreciated. Dept believes presence American observer
                                Repub territory important this <pb facs="0376" n="362" xml:id="pg_362"/> crucial time; suggests you devise means
                                sending member staff ConGen to Repub territory soonest to bridge
                                this difficult moment pending the reestablishment of <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> contact with Repub authorities
                                in such manner as will not be misinterpreted or excite speculation.
                                Dept believes Davies’ training suggests desirability his choice this
                                assignment. Coordinate this assignment with Cochran.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>